page.title: 14TYPICAL DAY-ROBERT REINELT
page.content: A typical day in my life begins at five o'clock, when I get up and feed my dogs.I have breakfast, get dressed into trousers,shirt,socks,and a jumper.Then I wash with soap and a flannel.About half-past eight I go to school and play football with a round ball.School starts at 9:05am.We read first,then we have maths.At 10:40am we have a break for fifteen minutes.We have lunch at noon.My lunch is sandwiches,crisps,and a chocolate biscuit.School finishes at 3:15pm.When I get home I watch T.V.or go out to play with my friend.When I come in I have my tea at about 6:15pm,then I go out again until 8:30-8:45pm. I go to bed at 9:15pm.
